directions: In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients and mix thoroughly. I use my hands so I can make sure all the flavors are even throughout the meat mixture.
Form 10 meatballs (about 2″ in diameter) and place onto your skewers. If you are using wooden skewers, make sure to soak them for about 10-15 minutes so that they don’t burn in the oven.
Place your skewers onto a aluminum foil lined pan and refrigerate for a minimum of 30 minutes. You can refrigerate them for as long as 12 hours.
After refrigerating, preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Bake the kebobs for about 15 minutes.
ingredients: Per meatball: 84 calories, 6g fat, .5g carbs, 7g protein
title: Lamb & Turkey Meatball Kebobs
